commit.message: Fix 2 player final score screen text
Use system mouse acceleration curve

Rewrite audio mixing

Audio output is no longer constrained to N * 11025 Hz.  Sounds are now resampled
to the output sample rate rather than just repeating each sample N times.

Audio mixer now uses only integer math.  Sound effects mixing is now slightly
less prone to clipping because all the channels are mixed before clipping.

Volume settings are now on a logarithmic rather than linear scale.

Loudness Sound System is now updated at 69.5 Hz rather than 70 Hz.  The
documentation says to update it at 70 Hz, but Tyrian typically updated it every
0x4300 cycles of the x86 PIT, which is approximately 69.565 Hz.
Rename menu item for consistency
Refactor delay timers
Use MSVC C compiler
Fix code style
Fix pause causing filter to apply to wrong surface
Render initial black screen
Speed up first logo fades
Fix not handling SDL events during palette fades
Change code style
Rename "OpenTyrian" menu item and menu to "Setup"
Fix build when WITH_NETWORK is false
